1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
MeetingMind -- an AI meeting memory agent built on EverMemOS.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,000
It helps you record meetings, extract commitments, and search memories, so you never forget a detail.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:15,500
Let's start with the Dashboard, a complete overview of all meetings, commitments, and contacts.

4
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:22,000
Three meetings, fifteen commitments, seven contacts, all your key data at a glance.

5
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Click into a meeting to see the AI-generated summary and every commitment extracted from the conversation.

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:35,000
Each commitment is labeled with its direction, whether you owe it or it's owed to you.

7
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:42,000
Now let's submit a new meeting. Fill in the title, date, participants, and meeting notes.

8
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:50,000
After submitting, the backend processes automatically, storing meeting content into EverMemOS as persistent memory.

9
00:00:50,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Meanwhile, the AI generates a summary and extracts all commitment items from the notes.

10
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:07,000
Processing complete. The AI extracted four commitments, each with an owner, due date, and direction.

11
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:16,000
Switch to the Commitments page, where all commitments across every meeting are consolidated and trackable.

12
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:22,000
Pending, overdue, completed. The full lifecycle of every promise, at a glance.

13
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:30,000
The Contacts page shows all meeting participants. Click any contact to see their full interaction timeline.

14
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:38,000
Here is Alice Chen's profile, showing her meetings and open commitments.

15
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:46,000
Next is the core feature: AI Briefing, generating an intelligent briefing for any contact.

16
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:55,000
The system retrieves relevant memories from EverMemOS, combines them with open commitments, and streams the briefing in real time.

17
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:03,000
Review everything before your next meeting, so you walk in fully prepared.

18
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:12,000
Finally, Search Memory. Enter keywords and a contact name to perform semantic search directly against EverMemOS.

19
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Searching for roadmap and Redis, EverMemOS returns matching episodic memory fragments.

20
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:32,000
All memories are retrieved through hybrid search, combining semantic understanding with keyword matching for precise recall.

21
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:44,000
MeetingMind. Let AI remember every meeting and track every commitment, so nothing falls through the cracks.
